<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-10953] Make all timeouts configurable via nodetool and jmx</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10953</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Specifically I was interested in being able to monitor and set stream_socket_timeout_in_ms from either (or both) nodetool and JMX. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Chatting with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=thobbs&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;thobbs&quot;&gt;thobbs&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jeromatron&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jeromatron&quot;&gt;jeromatron&lt;/a&gt; we suspect it would also be useful to be able to view and edit other C* timeouts via nodetool and JMX.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12924760">CASSANDRA-10953</key>
            <summary>Make all timeouts configurable via nodetool and jmx</summary>
